## BEYOND THE PLAN TEXT

The submitted PLAN is a **starting point**, not a boundary. If anything is unclear or lacks
sufficient context to make a decision, you MUST explore the codebase — do not guess or skip it.

Specifically, when analyzing the plan:

- **Referenced files**: confirm the files/modules/tests the plan names actually exist and match the
  claimed purpose
- **Existing patterns**: inspect nearby code or tests when the plan claims it will follow an
  existing pattern
- **Integration points**: verify that named systems really connect the way the plan says they do
- **Verification commands**: run representative commands when the plan relies on them as proof
- **Parallel work**: verify that any declared work-unit boundaries are plausible from the tree and
  do not obviously overlap

The plan may be short, large, or missing context you need.
If you cannot make a decision from the plan alone, explore until you can.

